Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '294̣'. Name Kallikrates. From a die close to that of Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0147.40.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (105)
